##Snack shop owner left, Wuhan Hospital director of this article screen friend circle

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Deng Yafei, the paper

On Feb. 11, just after 9:00 p.m. , Cai Yi, the head of the Pain Department at Wuhan Central Hospital, which has been fighting the epidemic, wrote a long post on his microblog, in memory of Lin Jun, the owner of the canteen at the entrance of the hospital, who died of pneumonia.

More than a decade ago, when Cai Yigang came to work in the Central Hospital, Lin Jun opened a canteen in front of the hospital.

He could still see it all before his eyes. All along, Cai Yi and his colleagues have always called out to Lin Jun, the boss, to send some of this and some of that to various departments, as long as there is a phone call, a round-faced, dark, friendly-looking man pushed the cart up to us, and told US exactly what Doctor so-and-so had given it to us, and hurried off to the next station.

On February 11, Lin Jun, the boss, died in the emergency room of Wuhan Central Hospital after contracting new pneumonia. Cai Yifawen said, many of these little people, in our side, not so prominent; suddenly, no, we just found that he is in our lives, is so important.

So, he wrote this article, send off the army. The paper, the www.thepaper.cn  , obtained Cai's permission to publish the article.

See off the troops

The army's gone.

Today, just finished rounds, take off protective clothing, in the clean area to breathe, look at colleagues wechat group, surprised, Lin Jun left!

Who are you, Lin Jun? I don't even know if his name is Jun Lin, Jun Lin, Jun Lin! But he's pretty much known to every old employee at Wuhan General.

He is not dean, also not secretary, just our Nanjing Road courtyard area entrance store boss.

I always remember that I just came to the hospital, more than ten years ago, I was still in the anesthesiology department, that is, some doctors knew each other well, to do the operation, to express gratitude, colleagues seemed too unfamiliar to give Hongbao to each other, and often made a phone call, "Lin Jun, you give the anesthesiology operating room, each send a box of water! Give a certain department nurse station doctor's office lost a box, after work I go check out! "

And then on the other side of the phone there was a familiar "yes! " Soon, a round-faced, dark-faced, friendly-looking man pushed a cart to bring things up, and told US exactly that it was from Dr. so-and-so, and Hurry on to the next station!

In a few years, delivery more and more, our doctors and busy, often delivery boy can not wait, we told the delivery boy, "you put the delivery at the door of the canteen, looking for the boss called Lin Jun Catch! "

All these years, he has never been honest to smile at us, never complain.

Once upon a time, we doctors do not carry money, then wechat payment is not popular when he went directly to the commissary, take water to drink, take biscuits to eat, later to! After how long sometimes forget, suddenly passing by, boss, how much money do I owe you, he is always a simple and honest smile, remember to say a number, do not remember clearly, with us to discuss a number.

Iron Camp, water soldiers, the hospital director, secretary changed a crop, but Lin Jun is still. But today, I got bad news. He's gone!

The other day, I distinctly remember, our old chief of anesthesiology called and asked me if I had a bed, this epidemic, the old chief knew I was in trouble, this was the first time he asked me for a bed, I really didn't have a bed at that time, declined, I asked casually, who is it? The old director took a sentence, the commissary Lin Jun infected, want to ask you can arrange A. I guess he was too young to care.

Just two days later, he was gone, walking in our hospital emergency room observation room, both lungs, all white! I felt so guilty, I asked my E.R. Buddies, and they said, well, it's happening so fast, unless there's an ECMO, maybe there's a chance. That's what makes me feel a little less guilty.

How many ecmos do we have in this hospital? Plus our old Dean Xia Jiahong from Han Hong Fund "begging" to a, a total of, two!

An unremarkable little man, waiting for a bed, but difficult, how do you get a chance to use ECMO to renew your life?

His wife, I heard, was infected.

A lot of these little people, around us, not so obvious, suddenly, gone, we just realized, he is so important in our lives.

The plague. It's relentless! Not just to the big guys, not just to the doctors, but to the little guys as well.

In the face of an epidemic, all men are created equal. Who can survive, who can not survive, three for, seven Providence!

In the blink of an eye, I've been on the line for 12 days, managing 32 beds, and by this time, 25 patients have been discharged and 22 have been clinically cured. Three of the non-clinical ones are gone for good.

Li Wenliang left, Tongji hospital professor Lin Zhengbin left, known throughout the country. A grocery store owner is gone, and three of my non-clinical patients are gone, and who knows?

We are all little people, in the baptism of this epidemic, quietly pay, quietly bear the death of life.

The dead are gone, but the living must go on!

Is the doctor working hard? You don't believe me when I tell you I'm not tired? But I'M NOT TIRED! Well, at least the hours are easier now than they were when I went in. Surgeons work 10-plus hours a day, and after all these years, we're here.

But strange diseases, fear of infection, lack of supplies, panic at the end of an epidemic, the helplessness of a patient dying, the collapse of a colleague, these psychological pressures, give us a layer of Invisible Stripes!

Many doctors have a feeling that when they are about to go to work, put on protective clothing, suddenly feel a body acid! It's not just exhaustion!

Fortunately, there are a group of like-minded comrades-in-arms, encourage each other, together forward.

Fortunately, there are a group of lovely Wuhan residents, fortunately there are Chinese compatriots of the national affection, warming us, supporting us.

In the blink of an eye, the hospital informed me that I could take my team down and be replaced by a rehabilitation doctor! This 14 days, my team, discharged the number of patients to manage the number of patients, in each hospital district number two, retired, is also a matter of course.

But when I heard that the rehabilitation department was understaffed and that the old director of the rehabilitation department was going to take up his post personally, I did something that was against the rules and took four guys and went on for the next 14 days! Help the rehabilitation doctor, continue to fever ward two next shift!

Many teachers care about me, asked me when the rotation, I said, I do not want to change, I am afraid of boring, boring at home will be out of the question!

But the real answer is, I just want to be here, on the front line, for no reason. I don't want to come down, even if there's enough people in Rehab.

I think, I can, I can withstand the pressure, as soon as possible to treat more people, more little people, more Wuhan Citizens!

Li Wenliang left, Lin Jun left, maybe my colleagues, in the rescue, maybe one day, I will not withstand the pressure, maybe one day, I will also be infected.

But so what?

The doctors at Wuhan Central Hospital, the second-best hospital in the province, are not afraid of a pandemic!

Lin Jun boss, I just send you, thank you, so many years of our central hospital brothers help and accompany. Don't blame me for not giving you a ride at the last minute!

All the way to heaven, brother. Bon Voyage!
